          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>London</placeName>
                                        <date>19th Adar 5611</date>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <date>21st Feby 1851</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>Revd and Dear Sir,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">In compliance with your request and indeed<lb/> I
                                        consider it no more than a duty on my part towards you to
                                        acquaint<lb/> you that on <date>Monday</date> afternoon last
                                        I received yr. Packet a letter from <persName>Mr.
                                                  H.</persName><lb/>
                                        <date>Feby 5th</date>: I have very little time left on my
                                        hands now, I must most fervently pray<lb/> and entreat you
                                        to excuse haste and writing, as I have been so very<lb/>
                                        busy this day; in other duties and replying to <persName>Mr.
                                                  H.</persName> that it is approaching to
                                                  <add>שבת</add><lb/> but I will give you some
                                        little extracts of his letter for <hi rend="underline">your
                                                  guidance</hi> Trusting<lb/> to your honor and
                                        integrity that you will not make use of my name neither<lb/>
                                        in this case, or in the other of <persName>M.</persName> for
                                        heaven be my witness that there is no harm<add>?</add><lb/>
                                        but <sic>dont</sic> wish my name in question since we have
                                        all <hi rend="underline">some good friends</hi> always<lb/>
                                        on the <hi rend="underline">look out</hi>. therefore my Dr.
                                        friend let it be <add>סוד ה' ליראיו</add> the information is
                                        for<lb/> your guidance at the same time I assure you from
                                        the 1st syllable to the last<lb/> there is not one
                                        disrespectful to you, on the contrary he speaks
                                        high—where<lb/> I said to him in my letter <del>he
                                                  replies</del>
                                        <hi rend="underline">that none should be revered unless
                                                  for</hi><lb/> high moral &amp; religious
                                        diligency" "<hi rend="underline">a man in holy office should
                                                  be raised &amp;</hi><lb/>
                                        <hi rend="underline">not lowered</hi>—he replies, "no
                                        removal has taken place—that nothing has been<lb/> done to
                                        lower our former Hazan in the estimation of the world
                                        indeed—and<lb/> so <persName>Mr. H</persName> goes on
                                        replying on my remarks—<sic>than</sic> he goes on informing
                                        me<lb/> I may say, almost the same as you did in your first
                                        letter. I will go on now with fewer traits<lb/> "In the
                                        first place not a person in the whole congregation says or
                                        can<lb/> say aught against <persName>Mr. Leeser's</persName>
                                        reputation."—I flattered myself<lb/> that I was and that
                                                  <persName>Mr Leeser</persName> also considered me
                                        his friend—</p>
                              <p>I feel satisfied that the congregation will not again find a
                                        person<lb/> combining all the qualities of a Hazan and
                                        lecturer and possessing<lb/> the talents of <persName>Mr.
                                                  Leeser</persName> and no one desires or can
                                        detract from his<lb/> merits he has done more for the Jews
                                        in <placeName>America</placeName> than any other</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>Hazan in these <placeName>United States</placeName> and a
                                        testimonial &amp;c &amp;c<lb/> "but I fear he has gone too
                                        far to heal the asperity of feeling with<lb/> which he has
                                        spoken of so many of the members since he has<lb/>
                                        <hi rend="underline">ceased to be our Hazan</hi>." so far
                                        for the extracts I replied to<lb/> his obliging letter on
                                        every point that I would not arrogate on<lb/> me the office
                                        of a Judge, and indeed was I asked to form a just<lb/>
                                        intimate of the subject I should hear both sides <add>שמע בן
                                                  אחיכם</add> I was<lb/> an advocate for moderation
                                        &amp; a reconciliation that I considered you an<lb/> honor
                                        to the house of <placeName>Israel</placeName> at large not
                                        only in <placeName>America</placeName> and you<lb/> have
                                        been <add>נר ישראל</add> and that after 20 years in office
                                        that the<lb/> misunderstanding between you and the
                                        congregation should be within a<lb/> nut shell (as he
                                        expresses it) I could not but regard not only with<lb/>
                                        regret but as a calamity I entertained the hope that he
                                        would continue his<lb/> kind regards towards you and so on.
                                        I must shorten my letter but I<lb/> think you have enough of
                                        it, it appears that they are exasperated<lb/> at your
                                        exposing them in the Occident, I hope it will all be
                                        peace<lb/> yet. Let me once more as a brother, friend,
                                                  <sic>reccomend</sic> you give in a little<lb/> and
                                        hope you will be restored which will be the happiest news
                                        you<lb/> will give me. Again let me request your secrecy <hi
                                                  rend="underline">particularly</hi> what<lb/> I
                                        might have wrote of <persName>M.</persName> as it is only
                                        true, but still as he is a friend and<lb/> a good young man
                                        I <sic>dont</sic> wish him to know that nay thing about him
                                        was<lb/> utterd by me <add>אפילו דבר קטן</add> I also must
                                        acquaint you that <persName>Mr. H.</persName> knows nothing
                                        of<lb/> your having informed me all in your first letter so
                                        let it stand as it is,<lb/> please to favor me with your
                                        reply and that matters have taken a favorable<lb/> change.
                                                  <persName>M.</persName> sets off on
                                                  <date>Saturday</date> next from
                                                  <placeName>Liverpool</placeName> you will please
                                        to let</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>know if you have seen <persName>Mr. H.</persName> I must confess
                                        that his letter is of a <add>?</add><lb/> and that his
                                        feelings are respectful towards you. Wishing you every
                                        success</p>
                              <p rend="indent(7)">I remain</p>
                              <p rend="indent(7)">yours most truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)">
                                        <persName role="author">D Meldola</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>I must add that I wrote to <persName>Mr. H.</persName> that as<lb/>
                                                  "<hi rend="underline">since my first reading your
                                                  works I entertaind</hi><lb/>
                                        <hi rend="underline">the highest respect for your name" the
                                                  greatest esteem".</hi> I believe I did my duty
                                        towards<lb/> you as much as a father, now you must do the
                                        same towards me as a son take<lb/> my advice <sic>dont</sic>
                                        be too hard get <persName>Mr. H.</persName> your friend
                                        again, give in a little, and <sic>dont</sic><lb/> allow your
                                        opponents to have their way, I wish I was there to impress
                                        all this on your<lb/> mind for it is only <add>אורייתא הוא
                                                  דקא מרתחא כך</add> abandon this for a while
                                                  <add>וחזקת והיית לאיש וכל אשר אתה עושה ה' מצליח
                                                  אכת"ו</add><lb/>
                                        <add>Hebrew</add></p>
                              <pb n="4"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>America</placeName>
                              </p>
